Alarm Description (English): Alarm (Critical) generated by VR when a train stops at a station and is considered to have a major ahead against the schedule. The amount of time considered to be a major ahead is configurable and the alarm will only be issued if the system is in schedule regulation mode, the option to alarm major ahead is on, and the vehicle is not in the depot.
Routing: User(s) who owns the territory where the alarm  event occurred
Inactive Condition:
* Major Ahead is no longer reported 
* System is switched to headway mode 
* System is switched to no regulation mode 
* Vehicle regulation is active

Taipei Circle Line Alarm List (English): <PVID><TID> consist <CONSIST> reported does not match a valid train consist configuration in ATS.
Alarm Description (English):
The vehicle count or configuration reported for a given train in the "Train configuration" (Type 166) message does not match any valid train consist configured in the ATS Subsystem.

The "Train configuration" (Type 166) message reports the unit count and then a listing of the units in order from front to back in the train.  For each unit the message reports the units ID and polarity.  Using this information, the alarm will create a <CONSIST> tokan that displays the units in the order reported, and lists the uni ID and polarity.

For example: "101(+),102(-),143(-)"
Routing: Dispatcher, Supervisor, SysManager, Maintainer, Instructor, Trainee
Inactive Condition: Consist reported for the applicable train in the "Train Configuraiton" (Type 166) message matches a valid train consist in the ATS Subsystem.
